arithmetic stillness (D* std deviation 3.26e-08, near-zero) coexists with its strongest
periodic structure. Stillness and periodicity are independent dimensions: the Sarabande is
simultaneously the most spatially cohesive and the most temporally periodic movement in
the corpus.
The Prélude. Dominant period at lag 11 (strength 0.1047) with a secondary signal at lag 3
(strength 0.1008). Bach’s arpeggiated figures — 8 notes per bar, repeated — produce the
lag 3 signal (the basic arpeggic unit). The lag 11 signal reflects cross-bar motivic structure.
The mechanical repetition of the opening is arithmetically imprinted.
Clair de Lune. Dominant period at lag 3 (strength 0.0696). Clair de Lune is written in 9/8 —
compound triple time, three groups of three. The tensor detected the triplet grouping
without being told the time signature. Debussy’s impressionist fluidity contains more
periodic structure than expected — the 9/8 metre leaves its arithmetic trace.
Literary works. Keats’ iambic pentameter — which might be expected to produce a lag 2
signal (the iambic foot) — registers only 0.0249. Carroll’s rhyme scheme produces a weak
lag 8 signal (0.0325). Dylan Thomas near-noise at lag 1 (0.0357). The tensor is detecting
musical metre specifically. Linguistic metre, even as regular as iambic pentameter, does not
produce comparable periodic structure in the J stream.
The predicted ordering confirmed:
Most periodic: Bach Sarabande (lag 7, strength 0.1202)
Bach Prélude (lag 11, strength 0.1047)
Musical middle: Clair de Lune (lag 3, strength 0.0696)
Text near-noise: Thomas, Carroll, Keats (0.02-0.04)
What the tensor adds to the stylometric portrait:
The existing portrait characterises works by clustering rate (structural repetition) and D* std
deviation (attractor tightness). The tensor autocorrelation adds a third independent
dimension: temporal periodicity of the ternary event sequence. A work can score high on all
three (Bach Suite — strong clustering, tight Sarabande, strong periodicity), or show
independence across dimensions (Keats — low clustering, tight D*, near-zero periodicity).
The three dimensions together constitute a more complete stylometric fingerprint than any
single measure. No new machinery required — the J stream was already there.
This addendum supplements the Honest Scope section of the main note. The tensor
autocorrelation was computed on the same J streams used for all other analyses. Full code
available at unitambo.wordpress.com.
